weren't present
in the developing countries.

50
00:04:08,175 --> 00:04:09,165
Yes?

51
00:04:11,545 --> 00:04:12,570
Hi.

52
00:04:12,646 --> 00:04:13,944
Come in.

53
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:27,487
Paper. Uh, sorry it's late.

54
00:04:28,728 --> 00:04:29,718
Why is it late?

55
00:04:30,763 --> 00:04:33,233
I had some personal
issues to deal with.

56
00:04:36,569 --> 00:04:38,665
I'm sorry, but I can't accept it now.

57
00:04:40,906 --> 00:04:42,169
I mean, I... I really had a...

58
00:04:42,241 --> 00:04:43,231
I'm sorry.

59
00:04:56,921 --> 00:05:00,861
Uh, you know you still haven't given us
the syllabus yet?

60
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,257
I know.

61
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,291
Yeah?

62
00:05:40,632 --> 00:05:41,657
Hello, Walter.

63
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:42,666
Hi, Charles.

64
00:05:42,734 --> 00:05:43,827
You got a sec?

65
00:05:43,901 --> 00:05:44,926
Sure.

66
00:05:46,036 --> 00:05:47,231
Walter, Shelley can't make it down

67
00:05:47,304 --> 00:05:49,240
to the NYU conference
to present your paper.

68
00:05:49,306 --> 00:05:51,071
I'm gonna need you to cover for her.

69
00:05:51,241 --> 00:05:52,938
Why can't she go?

70
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:56,039
She's been put on bed rest
till she has the baby.

71
00:05:56,113 --> 00:05:59,244
I wish I could, but now is not
a good time, Charles.

72
00:05:59,316 --> 00:06:01,912
Well, I understand,
but you co-authored the paper,

73
00:06:01,985 --> 00:06:03,044
and the Dean wants it presented.

74
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,418
He wants to keep
Shelley on track for tenure.

75
00:06:04,688 --> 00:06:07,854
I just don't think I can,
with the start of classes and my book.

76
00:06:08,925 --> 00:06:11,328
