94
00:10:08,993 --> 00:10:10,929
I'm... I'm... I'm not going to hurt you.

95
00:10:10,995 --> 00:10:13,022
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

96
00:10:13,096 --> 00:10:14,496
This is my apartment.

97
00:10:14,564 --> 00:10:16,056
This apartment does
not belong to you!

98
00:10:16,132 --> 00:10:17,930
- How did you get in here?
- My name is Walter Vale.

99
00:10:18,001 --> 00:10:19,994
- I have keys! This is my apartment!
- What the fuck!

100
00:10:20,069 --> 00:10:22,302
Ow! Ow! God! Aah! Please!

101
00:10:22,372 --> 00:10:23,601
- Zainab!
- I'm in here!

102
00:10:23,673 --> 00:10:25,107
- Shut up!
- Aah!

103
00:10:25,174 --> 00:10:26,905
- Shut up!
- All ri... Okay. Okay.

104
00:10:26,976 --> 00:10:28,035
Okay. Okay.

105
00:10:28,110 --> 00:10:29,135
Who are you?

106
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:30,406
<i>Qu'est-ce que c'est ça?</i>

107
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,607
<i>Ça va?</i>

108
00:10:31,681 --> 00:10:32,614
<i>Oui, ça va.</i>

109
00:10:32,682 --> 00:10:33,615
<i>C'est qui?</i>

110
00:10:33,683 --> 00:10:34,946
<i>J'étais dans mon bain.</i>

111
00:10:35,018 --> 00:10:36,077
<i>Lui, il était là.</i>

112
00:10:37,086 --> 00:10:38,179
- Did you touch her?
- What?

113
00:10:38,253 --> 00:10:39,448
- Motherfucker, did you touch her?
- No! No! No!

114
00:10:39,521 --> 00:10:40,990
<i>II ne m'a pas touchée.</i>

115
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:43,254
<i>Mais comme il est entré,</i>
<i>il a dit qu'il avait la clé.</i>

116
00:10:43,325 --> 00:10:44,954
Do you have keys?

117
00:10:45,028 --> 00:10:46,621
Yes, of course I have keys.
This is my apartment.

118
00:10:47,696 --> 00:10:48,960
- Show me your keys.
- All right.

119
00:10:49,032 --> 00:10:50,227
Here.

120
00:10:50,299 --> 00:10:51,631
I've had this apartment for 25 years.

121
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,135
So why haven't you been here?

122
00:10:53,202 --> 00:10:56,037
Because I live in Connecticut.
I haven't been down here in a very long time.

123
00:10:57,039 --> 00:10:58,166
Are you friends with Ivan?

124
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:00,038
Ivan. I don't... Who's Ivan?

125
00:11:01,710 --> 00:11:03,703
I'm sure he's called the police!

126
00:11:04,713 --> 00:11:06,478
- Did you call the police?
- No.

127
00:11:06,548 --> 00:11:08,380
- You did not call the police?
- No.

128
00:11:12,553 --> 00:11:13,647
And you don't know Ivan?

129
00:11:13,722 --> 00:11:15,156
No. Who is he?

130
00:11:15,223 --> 00:11:16,657
- He rented us this place.
- I don't know him.

131
00:11:16,724 --> 00:11:19,355
He said it belongs
to his friend who is out of town.

132
00:11:19,427 --> 00:11:20,417
I don't know who he is.

133
00:11:20,495 --> 00:11:22,226
This is my apartment. I assure you.

134
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:26,467
Shit!

135
00:11:26,534 --> 00:11:28,731
<i>Je t'ai déjà dit</i>
<i>de faire confiance à personne.</i>

136
00:11:29,003 --> 00:11:30,529
<i>T'as jamais signé</i>
<i>un contrat.</i>

137
00:11:34,742 --> 00:11:35,675
Shit.

138
00:11:36,744 --> 00:11:37,734
Hey, look.

139
00:11:40,414 --> 00:11:42,509
We don't want any trouble.

140
00:11:42,583 --> 00:11:44,245
We will get out of your apartment.

141
00:11:46,587 --> 00:11:48,488
Here. Take your keys.

142
00:11:49,589 --> 00:11:51,183
It's all a mistake. I'm sorry.

143
00:11:51,258 --> 00:11:52,191
Okay.

144
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:54,193
We will leave. Okay?

145
00:11:54,261 --> 00:11:55,752
Yeah, okay.

146
00:12:14,114 --> 00:12:15,413
How long have you lived here?

147
00:12:15,482 --> 00:12:17,178
Two months.

148
00:12:17,249 --> 00:12:18,775
We will pay you if you want.

149
00:12:24,057 --> 00:12:25,651
Yes, so, uh, we will go.

150
00:12:25,725 --> 00:12:27,387
I'm sorry, again.

151
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,793
Thank you for understanding.

152
00:12:37,369 --> 00:12:38,359
Go get the valise.

153
00:12:40,073 --> 00:12:41,062
Okay, okay.

154
00:12:44,643 --> 00:12:45,611
Good-bye.

155
00:12:45,678 --> 00:12:46,805
Good-bye.

156
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:44,793
Tarek.

157
00:13:44,869 --> 00:13:46,360
- Tarek.
- What?

158
00:13:50,874 --> 00:13:53,368
Uh... you left this in the apartment.

159
00:13:54,378 --> 00:13:55,368
Thanks.

160
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:02,143
So you know where
you're staying tonight?

161
00:14:04,387 --> 00:14:06,551
Yeah, sure. We're goin' to some friends'.

162
00:14:29,912 --> 00:14:31,848
You like classical music, huh?

163
00:14:31,914 --> 00:14:33,816
Yes.

164
00:14:33,883 --> 00:14:35,352
Me, too.

165
00:14:35,418 --> 00:14:36,545
Do you play the piano?

166
00:14:36,619 --> 00:14:38,384
No.

167
00:14:38,454 --> 00:14:39,387
Do you?

168
00:14:39,455 --> 00:14:42,187
Me? No. I play the djembe.

169
00:14:43,192 --> 00:14:43,921
Hmm.

170
00:14:44,193 --> 00:14:46,254
Okay. Good night.

171
00:14:47,429 --> 00:14:50,367
And thanks again for letting us stay.

172
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:53,495
Um... you saved me a lot of trouble,
if you know what I mean.

173
00:14:53,568 --> 00:14:57,201
We'll be out of your way
in a couple of days. Okay?

174
00:14:57,273 --> 00:14:58,707
Good night.

175
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:22,892
Good morning.

176
00:15:22,964 --> 00:15:23,954
Good morning.

177
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,903
I made some coffee.

178
00:15:27,969 --> 00:15:28,959
Thank you.

179
00:15:30,305 --> 00:15:34,746
And... have a good day.

180
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:35,798
Good-bye.

181
00:15:48,655 --> 00:15:49,884
Walter Vale.

182
00:15:53,927 --> 00:15:54,917
Thank you.

183
00:15:54,995 --> 00:15:56,828
And that will be on the last day
of the conference.

184
00:15:56,897 --> 00:15:58,594
I hope you can all attend.

185
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:01,934
And now I'd like to welcome
my distinguished colleague

186
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:04,234
and the winner
of the John Bates Clark Award...

187
00:16:04,304 --> 00:16:06,001
Professor Stephen Kriegman.

188
00:16:15,815 --> 00:16:16,805
Thank you, Shiva.

189
00:16:37,703 --> 00:16:38,635
Thank you.

190
00:16:38,705 --> 00:16:39,637
Excuse me.

191
00:16:39,705 --> 00:16:40,638
Yes?

192
00:16:40,705 --> 00:16:41,638
Mr. Vale?

193
00:16:41,706 --> 00:16:42,800
Yes.

194
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:45,812
Oh, my goodness. How are you?

195
00:16:45,877 --> 00:16:47,312
It's me.

196
00:16:47,380 --> 00:16:49,646
Jacob Koningsberg.
Do you remember me?

197
00:16:49,714 --> 00:16:51,877
- I'm sorry.
I... I used to live on the third floor

198
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:54,387
- with my mother.
Your wife used to give me piano lessons.

199
00:16:55,388 --> 00:16:56,981
Oh, right, right.

200
00:16:57,055 --> 00:16:58,991
How are you?

201
00:16:59,057 --> 00:17:00,993
Oh, my goodness.
I haven't seen you in so long.

202
00:17:01,059 --> 00:17:02,995
We thought that you
sold the place.

203
00:17:03,061 --> 00:17:03,994
You haven't met Sprinkles.

204
00:17:04,062 --> 00:17:05,827
This is Sprinkles. Say hello.

205
00:17:05,897 --> 00:17:07,058
Hello. How is your wife?

206
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,994
Oh, my wife passed away.

207
00:17:11,569 --> 00:17:12,902
Oh, I'm sorry.

208
00:17:14,406 --> 00:17:17,708
I'm very sorry.
My... My condolences to you.

209
00:17:17,776 --> 00:17:19,404
She was a lovely woman.

210
00:17:19,478 --> 00:17:22,882
Honestly, I could
listen to her play piano for hours.

211
00:17:22,948 --> 00:17:24,041
How is your mother?

212
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:27,485
My mother is fine.
Thank you very much.

213
00:17:27,551 --> 00:17:29,544
Thank you for asking. She's in Florida.

214
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:32,022
So I'm living alone now, and it's nice,

215
00:17:32,089 --> 00:17:35,027
but I tell you, there are so many
new people in this building,

216
00:17:35,092 --> 00:17:37,825
- and Mr. Sprinkles and I...
- It's nice to see you again, Jacob.

217
00:17:38,829 --> 00:17:39,854
It's good to see you.

218
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,091
Good to see you. Welcome home.

219
00:17:41,365 --> 00:17:42,629
Thank you.

220
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:43,929
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

221
00:17:55,112 --> 00:17:56,478
Stop it.

222
00:17:56,546 --> 00:17:57,707
Come on, honey.

223
00:18:07,123 --> 00:18:08,752
We find that,
under these circumstances,

224
00:18:08,825 --> 00:18:11,558
financial globalization
can be beneficial.

225
00:18:11,628 --> 00:18:14,691
Empirically, it's good institution
and quality of government

226
00:18:14,764 --> 00:18:16,893
that will allow third world countries

227
00:18:16,966 --> 00:18:19,129
to benefit and harvest
the fruits of globalization.

228
00:19:07,516 --> 00:19:09,110
Great stuff, huh?

229
00:19:09,184 --> 00:19:11,177
Maybe we should have 'em
come play inside.

230
00:19:12,687 --> 00:19:14,088
Uh, you coming?

231
00:19:14,156 --> 00:19:16,456
In a minute. Uh, I gotta make a call.

232
00:19:16,525 --> 00:19:18,119
- Oh. Uh, see you inside.
- Okay.

