she thinks something happened to me.

248
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:50,944
Yeah, I'll have a bit. Thanks.

249
00:20:51,951 --> 00:20:53,146
You sure you won't have some?

250
00:20:53,218 --> 00:20:54,277
I don't drink.

251
00:20:55,521 --> 00:20:57,753
She's a good Muslim. I'm a bad one.

252
00:20:58,958 --> 00:21:00,221
Are you finished?

253
00:21:00,292 --> 00:21:02,228
Yes. Uh... can I help you?

254
00:21:02,294 --> 00:21:05,232
No. Please.
It's the least I can do.

255
00:21:05,297 --> 00:21:07,631
Well, thank you for dinner.
It was very good.

256
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:09,294
- You're welcome.
- Thank you.

257
00:21:11,135 --> 00:21:13,071
So what's the conference about?

258
00:21:13,137 --> 00:21:15,232
Economic growth
in developing nations.

259
00:21:15,306 --> 00:21:18,039
That's us. Syria, Senegal.

260
00:21:20,144 --> 00:21:21,237
So have you written some books?

261
00:21:21,312 --> 00:21:23,248
Three, and I'm working on a fourth.

262
00:21:23,314 --> 00:21:24,908
- Four books.
- Mm-hmm.

263
00:21:24,982 --> 00:21:27,214
Wow. That's great.

264
00:21:28,986 --> 00:21:31,252
My father was a writer. A journalist.

